-Slightly stronger pets<br>
-Fast way to reclaim a misbehaving pet<br>
-Easy quests and the items themselves give small stat bonuses<br>
<br>
Disadvantages:<br>
-4 inventory slots taken up<br>
-All 4 add 14 extra weight (without a wt. reducing bag)<br>
-You have to remember to wield the correct one before summoning a Jobaber<br>
<br>
No, they won't turn your pet into an unstoppable little floating beast, but they do make them a tad more powerful (and larger in size).<br>
<br>
Also, at 60 I still carry around my Torch of Alna(?) because I occasionally summon the 49 fire pet.  It is also handy for quickly reclaiming a pet when I simply can't get it under control.  You should never be afraid to right-click a misbehaving pet to reclaim them and summon a new one, your group will thank you.  So yes, I'd very much recommend doing the quests.<br>
<br>
